FBIS4-15596 "drsov069_s_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 Georgia Investigators Leave for Scene Investigators Leave for Scene NC0904115294 Yerevan SNARK in English 0745 GMT 9 Apr 94 NC0904115294 Yerevan SNARK English BFN [Text] Tbilisi, April 9 (SNARK) -- The representatives of the Georgian authorities and a special investigating group of the Georgian Home Affairs Department left today for the Sadakhlo station where the Tbilisi-Yerevan train No. 675 was exploded at 3:00 a.m. The Head of the Transport Department of the Georgian National Security Department Colonel Ivan Kuldjanishvili told SNARK three passengers were killed and 5 wagons burnt as a result of explosion. The investigation has started.
